</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C321652CC90B6875FF7BFEB2C6FDFE38" pageId="8" pageNumber="483" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8436A7C90B6875FF7BFEB2C6FDFE38" blockId="8.[151,1437,151,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="483">
<emphasis id="B94FEAB5C90B6875FF7BFEB2C635FEF0" bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="8" pageNumber="483">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D24C90B6875FE6DFEB2C521FEF0" authorityName="Ma et Li" authorityYear="2020" box="[465,602,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Polemistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pediflavidus">
<emphasis id="B94FEAB5C90B6875FE6DFEB2C521FEF0" box="[465,602,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="483">pediflavidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is derived from the Latin words 
<emphasis id="B94FEAB5C90B6875FC72FEB2C481FEF1" box="[974,1018,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="483">pes,</emphasis>
genitive 
<emphasis id="B94FEAB5C90B6875FBDDFEB2C3E7FEF0" box="[1121,1180,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="483">pedis</emphasis>
(= leg) and 
<emphasis id="B94FEAB5C90B6875FA98FEB2C206FEF0" box="[1316,1405,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="483">flavidus</emphasis>
(= yellowish), referring to the legs yellowish to reddish brown except coxae black, one of the main recognition characters of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
